Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the @diced British chicken breast{260%g}, ~{8-10%mins}. Season with
@salt{} and @black pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling
raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, in a #bowl{}, combine the @coleslaw mix{120%g}, @rice vinegar{15%ml},
@sambal paste{15%g}, @olive oil{} and @sugar{1%tsp} (see pantry for both).
Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Set aside.

Crush the @salted peanuts{25%g} in the unopened sachet.

Once the chicken is cooked, stir the @gochujang paste{30%g} and @honey{1%tbsp}
(see pantry) into the pan. Remove from the heat.

Microwave the @plain taco tortillas{6} for 850W: ~{50%secs} / 750W: ~{1%min}. If
you don't have a #microwave{}, just enjoy them cold.

Transfer the tortillas to your #serving plates{}.

Spread on the @mayonnaise{3%tbsp} (see pantry).

Top with some @wild rocket{40%g}, then the chicken and sambal slaw.

Sprinkle over the peanuts to finish. Enjoy!